The code should be as follows:
```julia-repl
using DataFrames

function count_model_rows(df_cars)
    # Group the data by model and count how many rows there are for each model.
    df = groupby(df_cars, :model);
    return combine(df, nrow => :count);
end;
```
This function groups `df_cars` by `model`, then counts the number of rows in each group using [combine](https://dataframes.juliadata.org/latest/man/split_apply_combine/#DataFrames.combine). The result is a DataFrame with two columns: `model` and `count`.
